
[1]tolerance

   TOL'ERANCE, n. [L. tolerantia, from tolero, to bear.] The power or
   capacity of enduring; or the act of enduring.

   Diogenes one frosty morning came to the market place shaking, to show
   his tolerance.

   [Little used. But intolerance is in common use.]
